name: IM NAYEON
content: TWICE Nayeon, who shines her special presence from her name, will debut as a solo artist on June 24, 2022.Nayeon will release her first mini-album – “IM NAYEON” – thanks to the longing and cheering of numerous domestic and international K-pop fans. “IM NAYEON”, her first solo album, means “I’M NAYEON” and “Lim Nayeon”, her full name, at the same time. It stands out for the charming attitude, competence, and confidence of Nayeon, a “born to be a star”, which can be fully explained by her name alone.

name: Doughnut
content: "Doughnut" is a song recorded by South Korean girl group Twice. It is the group's ninth Japanese maxi single, featuring three other tracks. It was pre-released for digital download and streaming on December 3, 2021, by Warner Music Japan as a single from their upcoming Japanese full-length album Celebrate. The single and its B-side, "Wonderful Day", were physically released on December 15 in Japan.

TWICE’s deep love for the fans is expressed throughout the new album, including the album title!- “SCIENTIST”, the title song, sings the conclusion of the nine members after contemplating love! Love is clear, not complicated!- It contains well-prepared 17 songs including songs contributed by NAYEON, JIHYO, DAHYUN, and CHAEYOUNG, “CANDY”, a song devoted to the fans (fan song), & the first unit songs of TWICE!- TWICE unleashes its unrivaled presence with the “Formula of Love: O+T=<3”, a full-length album after about one year, and “SCIENTIST”, a new song!

Doubles the unique charm of nine members with trendy visual + free atmosphere!
tracks: The Feels - Benny Benassi Remix Extended

name: Perfect World
content: Perfect World is the third Japanese studio album (fifth overall) by South Korean girl group Twice. It was released on July 28, 2021, by Warner Music Japan. The album features 10 tracks, including the title track, "Perfect World", and three previously released singles, "Fanfare", "Better", and "Kura Kura".

name: Taste of Love
content: TWICE Will Release “Taste of Love”, the 10th Mini Album, and “Alcohol-Free”, the Title Track on June 11th- The first new album of the representative K-pop girl group releases in 2021! Enchanting songs sung by TWICE- “Alcohol-Free”, the title track, is a “new TWICE-brand summer song” made by combining hip-hop with Bossa Nova- Lyrics of songs are solely written by Nayeon, Sana, Jihyo, and Dahyun & Globally renowned artists joined in this album! A masterpiece album that will hit the summer of 2021!

name: Kura Kura
content: "Kura Kura" ("dizziness") is a song recorded by South Korean girl group TWICE. It is the group's eighth Japanese maxi single, featuring three other tracks. It was pre-released for digital download and streaming on April 21, 2021, by Warner Music Japan. The single and its B-side, "Strawberry Moon", were physically released on May 12, 2021, in Japan.

name: CRY FOR ME

Singing the confused emotions of entangled love and hate!- A powerful magic of love shown by TWICE! Inescapable black-hole-like emotion!

name: BETTER
content: "Better" is a song recorded by South Korean girl group Twice. It is the group's seventh Japanese maxi single, featuring three other tracks. It was pre-released for digital download and streaming on November 11, 2020, by Warner Music Japan. The single was physically released on November 18, 2020, in Japan.

name: #TWICE3
content: #TWICE3 is the third Japanese compilation album released by South Korean girl group Twice. The album consists of Japanese and Korean versions of "Fancy", "Feel Special", "More & More", "Stuck In My Head", "21:29" and "The Best Thing I Ever Did". It was released on September 16, 2020, under Warner Music Japan.

name: Fanfare
content: Fanfare is the 6th Japanese single by South Korean girl group TWICE. The single was released on July 8, 2020, and the song "Fanfare" and its music video were released on June 19, 2020.

name: &TWICE (Repackage)
content: &TWICE -Repackage- is a repackage of TWICE's second Japanese studio album &TWICE. It was released on February 5, 2020 with "Swing" serving as the album's title track.The physical release comes in two versions: a regular CD edition and a limited CD+DVD edition.

name: &TWICE
content: &TWICE is the second Japanese studio album by TWICE. It was released on November 20, 2019 with "Fake & True" serving as the album's title track.The physical release comes in four versions: a regular CD edition, two limited CD+DVD editions (Types A and B) and a limited fanclub CD edition (available for ONCE Japan members only).

There is also a version limited to Japan "Once" member only, which they can choose between one individual member on the cover, or the Halloween cover.
